name: cutaneous plasmacytosis
description: cutaneous manifestation of plasmacytosis

name: cutaneous plasmacytosis
description: Plasmacytosis in the skin.

name: leydig cell tumor
description: Tumor derived from Leydig cells (M-8650/1).

name: steatosis
description: Abnormal retention of lipids within a cell. Physically apparent as lipid within liposomes of parenchymal cells.

name: apocrine metaplasia
description: Alteration of acinar epithelium of, for example, mammary tissue to resemble apocrine glands.

name: onychogryphosis
description: Hypertrophy of the nail bed resulting in abnormally long, curved and thickened nails.

name: hydronephrosis
description: Swelling of the kidneys when urine flow is obstructed in any of part of the urinary tract. Severe form of pyelectasia.

name: mastocytoma
description: mastocytoma

name: connective tissue replacement
description: Replacement of connective tissue by fibro-fatty deposits and scar tissue.

name: general immunodeficiency disease
description: general immunodeficiency disease

name: left/right axis defect
description: Left/Right (mediolateral) axis aberration of the normal symmetrical organisation of the body pattern.

name: hypersensitivity disease
description: Immune response resulting in tissue injury.

name: atypical hyperplasia
description: Presence of localised areas within for example adenomas showing characteristics of neoplastic (tumor) progression, eg focal carcinoma.

name: sebaceous adenoma
description: Adenoma of sebaceous cells; regular architecture of gland not mantained. Large numbers of immature germinative cells present. Mitoses. (M-8410/0).

name: soft tissue fibrosarcoma
description: Malignant tumor derived from pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells; fibroblasts, fibrocytes (M-8810/3).

name: Non-Lymphoid leukaemias
description: Neoplasms of non-lymphoid haematopoietic lineage. Must have at least 20% blast cells to meet this definition.

name: bilateral retinal degeneration
description: Retinal degeneration of both eyes.

name: central nervous system tumor
description: Neoplasm of the neurones, glia or meninges of the CNS.

name: cystic medial necrosis
description: Loss of muscle fibers and elastin in the media of the aorta, with accumulation of mucopolysaccharide.

name: carcinosarcoma
description: Possible origin from smooth muscle cells or pluripotential embryonic mesenchymal cells. May show up to three cellular componants including carcinoma and sarcoma type appearances. (M-8980/3).

name: lipofuscin deposition
description: Intracellular deposition of brown pigment granules probably representing lipid-containing residues of lysosomal digestion. Often age related.

name: sarcoma
description: A connective tissue neoplasm, usually highly malignant, formed by proliferation of mesodermal cells.

name: sarcoma
description: A connective tissue neoplasm, usually highly malignant, formed by proliferation of mesodermal cells.

name: developmental or adult structural  defect
description: Structural, physical or other general defect of prenatal development of the embryo and the placenta, or such as are acquired in the adult.

name: adenocarcinoma in situ
description: A noninvasive abnormal proliferation of glands believed to precede the appearance of invasive adenocarcinoma. (M-8140/2).

name: mucinous carcinoma
description: carcinoma derived from gastrointestinal epithelium with a high mucinous content. (M-8480/3).

name: germ cell tumor
description: Neoplasms derived from germ cells. May be gonadal or extragonadal and are derived from primordial germ cells.

name: ectopia
description: ectopia

name: trichofolliculoma
description: Basaloid neoplasm with numerous mature hair follicles and hair formation.

name: junctional epidermolysis bullosa
description: severe type of the disorder generally apparent at birth.Junctional epidermolysis bullosa involves defects in hemidesmosomes. t

name: gonadal somatic cell tumor
description: Neoplasms derived from the non-germ cell derived tissues of the testis and ovary.

name: dysplasia
description: Distortion or deficiency of the tissue or cellular architecture.

name: severe intra-epithelial neoplasia
description: Severe non-invasive malignancy associated changes in cell morphology and tissue architecture confined to the epithelium alone.

name: pneumonitis
description: An interstitial, granulomatous, fibrosing inflammation of the lung, especially of the bronchioles and alveoli.

name: leukaemia
description: leukaemia

name: karyomegaly
description: Abnormally increased nuclear size.

name: lymphedema
description: Accumulation of interstitial fluid caused by blockage or failure of the lymphatic system.

name: squamous metaplasia
description: Change of a glandular or mucosal epithelium into squamous epithelium.

name: mast cell tumor
description: mast cell tumor

name: serous exudate
description: Non-cellular fluid that filters from the circulatory system and accumulates in lesions or areas of inflammation.

name: sclerosis
description: Any pathological thickening or hardening of a tissue.

name: hemolysis
description: Rupture or disruption of erythrocytes with release of contents.

name: edema
description: An accumulation of an excessive amount of watery fluid in cells or intercellular tissues.

name: paraganglioma
description: A neoplasm composed of derivatives of CHIEF cells usually in single encapsulated nodular masses surrounded with sustentacular cells. ( M- 8711/0).

name: glomus tumor
description: glomus tumor

name: glomerulonephritis
description: Renal disease characterised by diffuse inflammatory changes in glomeruli not in response to an infectious agent or treatment.

name: polyp
description: A mass of tissue which projects outward or upward from the normal surface level being macroscopically visible as a hemispheroidal, spheroidal, or irregular moundlike structure growing from a relatively broad base or a slender stalk.

name: dysgerminoma
description: Undifferentiated germ cell tumor of the ovary composed of solid sheets of large polygonal cells with rim of clear cytoplasm (M-9060/3).

name: angiomyolipoma
description: Benign renal neoplasm composed of fat, vascular, and smooth muscle elements. Associated with tuberous sclerosis in humans. Aetiology unknown, but the combination of elements may reflect a lesion specific pattern of metaplasia. (M-8860/0).

name: embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma
description: Malignant mesenchymal tumor that morphologically and phenotypically resembles embryonal skeletal muscle.

name: meningioma
description: meningioma

name: myxomatous tumor
description: Neoplasms resembling primitive mesenchymal tissue with a soft mucous matrix.

name: fibromatosis
description: Systemic manifestation of MPATH: 407.

name: hypocalcification
description: Intrinsic abnormally low level of calcification in a tissue cf. MPATH: 48.

name: fibroepithelial tumor
description: Tumors with epithelial invaginations/linings and a fibrillary and fibrocytic stroma. (M-9000 - M-9030).

name: immunoblastic lymphoma
description: immunoblastic lymphoma

name: developmental dysplasia
description: Abnormal development (of organs or tissues) or an abnormal structure resulting from such growth.

name: cystadenoma
description: A benign neoplasm derived from glandular epithelium, in which cystic accumulations of retained secretions are formed. (M-8440/0).

name: pilomatricoma
description: Tumor composed of the epithelial components of the most proximal (trichogenic) portion of the hair follicle associated with an aberrent hair cortex type of cornification (ghost cells or shadow cells). The most primitive cellular component consists of basophilic cells having scanty cytoplasm and nuclei that occasionally overlap to some extent. In humans mineralisation is common.

name: focal pulmonary fibrosis
description: Various degrees of pulmonary interstitial fibrosis.

name: homoeotic change
description: Stricto sensu: replacement of one body part or tissue by an homologous structure or tissue, but commonly used incorrectly to describe non-homologous transformations better described as heterotopias or ectopias.

name: myelofibrosis
description: In mice the term refers to accumulation of fibrous connective tissue in the medullary cavity of bones; usually in old mice. In humans the term is synonymous with myeloid metaplasia.

name: sertoli cell tumor
description: Tumor derived from sex cord/stromal cells; Sertoli cells and can occur in both testis and ovary. (M-8640/1).

name: cytopenia with increased blasts
description: Haematopoietic proliferation with evidence of trilineage dysplasia. More than 20% should be blasts.

name: trabecular bone thickening
description: Thickening of trabecular bone.

name: cell and tissue damage process
description: Processes occurring during cell and tissue damage of either intrinsic or extrinsic etiology.

name: follicle center cell lymphoma
description: follicle center cell lymphoma

name: microvesicular lipidosis
description:
Variant form of hepatic steatosis. Hepatocytes partially or completely filled with numerous small lipid vacuoles. Affected hepatocytes may have a foamy  appearance.Small vacuoles do not normally displace the nucleus to
the periphery in contrast to macrovesicular lipidosis.

name: hepatocellular carcinoma
description: Malignant tumor derived from hepatocytes. (M- 8170/3).

name: spongiotrophoblast defect
description: Defect in size, cellular composition, function or organisation of the spongiotrophoblast zone of the placenta.

name: true hermaphrodite
description: possession of both ovary and testis due to primary sex determination defect

name: type III hypersensitivity
description: Tissue injury mediated by immune complexes. Generally involves immune complexes formed in the blood via antibodies encountering circulating antigens. Immune complexes then deposit in tissues (especially blood vessels and glomeruli), induce complement activation, and result in tissue injury.

name: skin embolism
description: Occlusion of vessels, usually small arterioles in the dermis by various emboli.

name: granular cell tumor/alveolar sarcoma
description: granular cell tumor/alveolar sarcoma

name: intravascular leiomyomatosis
description: Benign leiomyoma that invades vascular spaces. (M-8890/1).

name: neurofibrosarcoma
description: Malignant neoplasm derived from Schwann cells. (M-9540/3).

name: lymphoma
description: lymphoma

name: bronchioloalveolar adenoma
description: Benign epithelial neoplasm of the lung. (M-8140/1) 1.2.1.2 in MMHCC classification.

name: pigmentary incontinence
description: Release of melanin pigment in the dermis.

name: growth acceleration
description: Increase in the rate of growth of an organism, organ or tissue as a consequence of increased proliferation, reduced cell death, or a combination. Not due to an increase in cell size; see Hypertrophy MPATH: 159.

name: intraductal papilloma
description: Benign papilloma arising from ductal epithelium (M- 8503/0 ).

name: interstitial mineralization
description: Foci of mineralization within the interstitium of a tissue.

name: non-lymphoid hematopoietic sarcomas
description: Solid tumor mass composed of non-lymphoid haematopoietic cells.

name: transdifferentiation
description: Alteration in the differentiation of a cell or tissue already showing a different, recognisable, differentiated state.

name: papillary cystadenoma
description: A benign neoplasm derived from glandular epithelium, in which cysts contain folds or papillary projections into the lumen. (M-8450/0).

name: osteopetrosis
description: Excessive formation of dense trabecular bone and mineralized cartilage, especially in long bones, leading to obliteration of marrow spaces and to anemia with myeloid metaplasia and hepatosplenomegaly beginning in infancy, to bone fragility, and to progressive deafness and blindness.

name: precursor B cell neoplasms
description: Lymphoma originating from precursor B-cells.

name: epicardial mineralization
description: Deposition of minerals in the epicardium.

name: lymphangiectasis
description: A stretching and widening of the lymphatic vessels.

name: hepatic tumor
description: Tumors of the liver and biliary apparatus.

name: myofibroma
description: A benign localized neoplasm arising from the subcutaneous tissues and skeletal muscle. It is characterized by the presence of myofibroblastic hyperchromatic spindle cells, hylanized stroma formation, calcification, necrosis, and a multinodular growth pattern.

name: mesothelioma
description: Benign or malignant neoplasm derived from the lining cells of the pleura and peritoneum, composed of spindle cells or fibrous tissue which may enclose glandlike spaces lined by cuboidal cells. Epithelioid, fibrous, cystis, papillary, and sarcomatoid variants. (M- 9050/3).

name: amniotic fluid embolism
description: Occlusion of vessels caused by entry of amniotic fluid, cell and debris into the maternal circulation.

name: hepatic mid-zonal fatty metamorphosis
description: Fatty change in the mid-zonal region of the liver.

name: retinoblastoma
description: Malignant juvenile neoplasm of the eye derived from primitive retinal precursor cells. (M- 9510/3).

name: thrombosis
description: Presence of an occluding or mural thrombus in a blood vessel.

name: epithelial hyperplasia
description: Abnormal proliferation of epithelial cells and epithelial components.

name: myxosarcoma
description: A malignant neoplasm derived from pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells of connective tissue, consisting chiefly of polyhedral and stellate cells that are loosely embedded in a soft mucoid matrix. (M-8840/3).

name: papilloma
description: A benign tumor consisting of villous or arborescent outgrowths of fibrovascular stroma covered by neoplastic epithelial cells (M-8050/0).

name: nephroblastomatosis
description: nephroblastomatosis

name: nephroblastomatosis
description: Persistence of metanephrogenic blastema or its presence in the wrong place or at the wrong time. Associated with hyperplastic nephrogenic rests.

name: caseous necrosis
description: Necrosis characteristic of some inflammatory conditions which represents necrosis with loss of structure of the various cellular and tissue elements; affected tissue manifests a friable, crumbly consistency.

name: Harderian gland adenoma
description: Adenoma derived from acinar epithelium of the harderian gland. Papillary, cystic, cystic-papillary and acinar forms.

name: normal
description: Normal.

name: barbered
description: loss of hair resulting from a behavioral abnormality in which the mouse, or more often other mice mice in the same box, remove hairs, initially vibrissae, from each other.

name: immunodeficiency associated infection
description: Infection with bacteria, viruses or fungi subsequent to immunodeficiency.

name: obstruction and stenosis
description: Occlusion ( partial or complete) of a lumen or space, internally by a space occupying mass or, in the case of stenosis, by local reduction in the diameter of a vessel, duct or the intestine.

name: mucinous cystadenoma
description: A benign neoplasm derived from glandular epithelium, in which cystic accumulations of mucinous retained secretions are formed. (M-8470/0).

name: fracture and healing
description: Break in bone associated with exostoses.

name: neoplasm
description: A tumor resulting from abnormal and uncontrolled autonomous new cell growth (proliferation)that may be benign or malignant.

name: myeloproliferative disease
description: Non-reactive persistent accumulation of non-lymphoid haematopoietic cells in the blood which infiltrate the spleen and the bone marrow.

name: cardiac septation defect
description: Abnormality in the wall between the atria or ventricles, or defects in the truncoconal septum, of the heart; usually incomplete closure.

name: cytoskeletal defect
description: Defect in the structure or function of the cytoskeleton.

name: diffuse large B-cell lymphoma, immunoblastic type
description: Diffuse large B cell lymphoma with increased number of immunoblasts.

name: myoblastoma
description: myoblastoma

name: melanoma in situ
description: A potentially malignant lesion, melanoma in situ is the first phase of growth of melanoma, in which it is still confined to the epithelial domain (epidermis and adnexa) and has not passed through the basement membrane. (M-8720/2).

name: mature T-cell neoplasms
description: Non-thymic neoplasms of mature T cell origin.

name: paraphimosis
description: persistent retraction of the prepuce behind the glans penis

name: CNS progenitor tumor
description: Neoplasms derived from neuroepithelial precursors.

name: ecchymosis
description: A red/purple patch caused by extravasation of blood into the skin. Larger than petechiae.

name: partial abortion
description: Evidence of residual placenta in utero without embryo.

name: odontogenic tumor
description: odontogenic tumor

name: odontogenic tumor
description: Neoplasm arising from the tissues of the odontogenic apparatus. These tumors are derived from ectodermal tissue (epithelial tumors) or from mesodermal tissue (connective tissue tumors) or are composed of both components (mixed or composite odontogenic tumors) .

name: hypoplasia
description: Small organ or structure; failure to develop to normal size.

name: capillary hemangioma
description: Benign proliferation of capillaries made up of closely packed aggregations of capillaries, usually of normal caliber, separated by scant connective stroma.

name: metaplastic tissue
description: A tissue or group of cells in which there has been abnormal transformation of an fully differentiated adult cell or tissue of one kind into a differentiated tissue of another kind.

name: aortic body tumor
description: Paraganglioma arising in the CHIEF cells of the aortic body (M-8691/1).

name: synovial sarcoma
description: Malignant neoplasm occurring in close association with tendon sheaths and joint capsules. Biphasic in humans , showing a mixed spindle cell and epithelioid like morphology; this is not seen in rodents to date. (M-9040/3).

name: B cell neoplasms
description: B cell neoplasms

name: myeloid hyperplasia
description: Hyperplasia of myeloid lineage, usually in the spleen.

name: cell and tissue damage
description: The sum of morphological and functional disturbances induced by cell and tissue damage, either from intrinsic gene dysfunction or as a result of external factors.

name: hypertrophy
description: Increase in size or mass of a cell, tissue or organ without increase in cell proliferation. Cf. Hyperplasia MPATH: 133.

name: transitional cell papilloma
description: Pre-malignant lesion of transitional cells, papillomatous form ( M- 8120/1).

name: myositis
description: Inflammation of a muscle.

name: glaucoma; open angle
description: Failure of drainage of the eye for unknown reasons.

name: ovarian bursal cyst
description: Marked dilatation of the ovarian bursa.

name: acute inflammation
description: Inflammation with a recent onset, characterised histologically by primarily granulocyte infiltration, edema and hyperemia.

name: vasculogenesis defect
description: Defect in formation of blood vessels by vasculogenesis, proliferation or recruitment of endothelial cells.

name: abnormal intestine length
description: Abnormal length of the intestine.

name: eccrine gland adenoma
description: Benign neoplasm of the eccrine gland (M-8408/0).

name: piecemeal necrosis
description: Sensu; hepaticobiliary system. Loss and degeneration of hepatocytes at the portal-lobular interface producing a moth-eaten irregular appearance. Piecemeal necrosis is associated with a lymphocytic infiltrate.

name: small B-cell lymphoma
description: Diffuse accumulation of small mature B-cells.

name: small lymphocytic lymphoma
description: small lymphocytic lymphoma

name: inspissation
description: The drying, thickening  and coagulation of extracellular secretions or fluids.

name: hemangioendothelioma
description: hemangioendothelioma

name: alopecia
description: Absence of hair or loss of hair.

name: extraosseous plasmacytoma
description: Diffuse proliferation of mature plasma cells. Clonal by definition. Frequently found in IL6 transgenic mice. Characteristically involves spleen and nodes rather than peritoneum.

name: scoliosis
description: scoliosis is an abnormal curvature of the spine. The spine curves away from the middle or sideways.

name: glycogen deposition
description: Intracellular deposition of glycogen.

name: granulomatous arthritis
description: arthitis involving extensive macrophage infiltration into the joint.

name: ameloblastoma
description: Benign odontogenic epithelial neoplasm that histologically mimics the embryonic enamel organ but does not differentiate to the point of forming dental hard tissue. Histologically dominated by epithelial cells in a scant fibroblastic stroma. (M-9310/0).

name: Acinar adenocarcinoma
description: Tumor composed of small glandular clusters with small lumens.

name: systemic plasmacytosis
description: Abnormality of circulating plasma cells

name: systemic plasmacytosis
description: systemic manifestation of plasmacytosis. Disseminated in the circulation.

name: signet ring cell carcinoma
description: Adenocarcinoma of signet ring type arising from exocrine cells of the gastric mucosa or enterocytes of intestinal mucosa. (M-8490/3).

name: branching defect
description: Aberrant branch or branching pattern of a branched structure such as the bronchus.

name: osteochondroma
description: Benign bone tumor characterized by hyaline cartilage capped bony growths that project from the surface of the affected bone. (M-9210/0).

name: inflammatory polyp
description: A projecting mass of granulation tissue which may become covered by regenerating epithelium.

name: gastric adenomatous hyperplasia
description: Thickening of the glandular epithelium

name: spermatocytic seminoma
description: Neoplasm of the testis usually found within the tubule. Some debate as to whether it is of germ cell origin in contrast to classical seminoma. Three types of cells are identified in spermatocytic seminomas: those with small, intermediate, and large nuclei in humans. (M-9063/3).

name: pigmentation
description: Coloration, either normal or pathologic, of the skin or tissues resulting from a deposit of pigment.

name: hyperkeratosis
description: Thickening of the surface layers (stratum corneum) in the skin or other stratified squamous epithelium. Cf. ortho- and para-keratosis.

name: gingivitis
description: Inflammation of the tooth gum

name: prolapse
description: To sink down, said of an organ or other part. A sinking of an organ or other part, especially its appearance at a natural or artificial orifice.

name: intestinal metaplasia
description: Appearance of heterotopic intestinal epithelium.

name: cataract; capsular-epithelial
description: Proliferation of lens epithelium and capsule leading to fibrous metaplasia and anterior subcapsular cataract ( ASC) . Possible developmental origin.

name: hydrocephalus
description: Accumulation of water in the ventricles of the brain.

name: ectasia
description: Dilation of a tubular structure.

name: apocrine adenoma
description: Benign neoplasm of the epithelium of apocrine glands (M-8401/0).

name: intestinal intra-epithelial neoplasia
description: Histologically apparent areas of dysplasia that are not grossly visible (smaller than 0.5-1 mm). Lesions may involve single or multiple glands.

name: encephalomalacia
description: Softening of brain tissue, usually caused by vascular insufficiency or degenerative changes.

name: basal cell carcinoma
description: Malignant neoplasm of the basal cells of the epidermis with local invasion. (M-8090/3).

name: lysosomal defect
description: Defect in the structure or function of the lysosomes.

name: melena
description: Digested blood in the lumen of the stomach or small intestine, indicative of hemorrhage.

name: ependymoma
description: Neoplasm derived from the ependymal cells lining the ventricles and aqueduct of the brain and the central canal of the spinal cord. Malignant or benign. (M-9391/3).

name: amyloid deposition
description: Extracellular deposition of amyloid protein.

name: T large cell anaplastic lymphoma
description: Diffuse large pleiomorphic T cell lymphoma. This entity does not correspond to human anaplastic large cell lymphoma.

name: dystrophy
description: Regressive changes which may increase in severity, and which may result from defective nutrition or support of a tissue or organ.

name: intracellular and extracellular depletion
description: Loss or dispersion of specific intra- and extracellular substances.

name: synovioma
description: synovioma

name: pineocytoma
description: A tumor arising in the pineal gland that resembles normal pineal parenchyma. (M-9361/1).

name: pilocytic astrocytoma
description: Glial cell derived tumor composed of bipolar cells with long `hairlike` GFAP-positive processes. (M9421/1).

name: edematous cholecystitis
description: cholecystitis associated with edema

name: endodermal sinus tumor
description: Germ cell derived tumors resembling parietal or visceral yolk sac endoderm derivatives. Abundant eosinophilic matrix surrounding nests and cords of neoplastic cells. (M-9071-3).

name: plasmacytosis
description: Plasmacytosis is a hyperplastic condition in which there is an unusually large proportion of mature plasma cells in tissues, exudates, or blood.

name: plasmacytosis
description: A condition in which there is an unusually large proportion of plasma cells in tissues, exudates, or blood.

name: gynandroblastoma
description: gynandroblastoma

name: inter-ventricular septal defect
description: Failure of the inter-ventricular septum to completely close between the left and right ventricles.

name: epithelial metaplasia
description: Metaplasia occurring within epithelia.

name: lymphatic metastasis
description: Metastatic tumor in the lymphatic vessels or lymph nodes of unspecified origin.

name: furunculosis
description: Focal suppurative inflammation of the skin and subcutaneous tissues, enclosing a central slough or `core`.

name: healing and repair process
description: The process, normal or abnormal, of damage repair or wound closure.

name: immunopathological process
description: Inappropriate or aberrant activation or suppression of the immune or inflammatory response.

name: focal hyperplasia
description: Localised hyperplastic lesion. Polyclonal lesions are probably benign but clonal lesions may progress to malignancy.

name: sex cord tumor
description: sex cord tumor

name: fibroma
description: Benign neoplasm of fibroblasts/fibrocytes with poor/moderate cellularity. (M-8810/0).

name: glomangioma
description: Tumor derived from the capillary glomus with arteriovenous capillary anastomoses. Often characterized by multiple tumors resembling cavernous hemangioma (M-8712/0).

name: hemangiosarcoma
description: Malignant neoplasm derived from pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells or endothelial cells of blood vessels. (M-9120/3).

name: adenoacanthoma
description: Mixed tumor of glandular epithelia with squamous and glandular diffferentiation. (M-8570/3).

name: lipid deposition
description: Extra or intracellular deposition of lipid.

name: developmental and structural abnormality
description: Developmental and structural abnormalities occurring during embryonic development or during adult life.

name: adenocarcinoma
description: Malignant neoplasm of epithelial cells in glandular or glandlike pattern. (M-8140/3).

name: torsion
description: The twisting of a bodily organ or part on its own axis.

name: diverticulum
description: A blind ended outpouching through the wall of a tubular organ or bounded cavity.

name: basaloid follicular neoplasms
description: This is a new diagnostic term that the MMHC pathology panel felt best described a diagnostically challenging set of tumors that share the feature of being compose of basaloid cells showing follicular differentiation to some extent. These tumors are common in GEM involving the hedgehog signaling pathway and frequently have more than one of the histologic patterns listed below. The designation of benign and malignant has been excluded from the primary diagnosis purposely, as this is frequently difficult to determine in these characteristically well circumscribed tumors. The presence of a disorganized (non-palisaded) sheet-like growth pattern, tumor necrosis, or numerous mitoses are felt to represent malignant transformation.

name: teratoma
description: Generally benign germ cell derived tumors of male or female containing derivatives from all three germ layers with differentiation in the malignant form being poor. Malignant tumors are highly metatstatic. (M-9080/1).

name: Dysplasia
description: Dysplasia

name: hepatic peri-ductal inflammation
description: Inflammatory cell infiltrate around bile ducts within the liver.

name: hematopoietic/lymphoid malignancies/disorder
description: Proliferative disorders and malignancies of the lymphoid and non lymphoid haematopoietic lineages.

name: hygroma
description: Large cystic subcutaneous spaces usually found in the flexures, especially around the neck.

name: oncocytic metaplasia
description: Appearance of oncocytic cells in for example an epithelium or tumor.

name: thymic lymphoma
description: thymic lymphoma

name: obsolete
description: obsolete

name: cholesterol deposition
description: Intra or extracellular deposition of cholesterol.

name: granulation tissue
description: Newly formed connective (vascular or fibrous)tissue caused by inflammation or healing (repair) processes. Microscopically consists of capillaries fibroblastic cells and inflammatory cells.

name: disseminated intravascular coagulation
description: A syndrome consequent to uncontrolled activation of blood clotting factors leading to disseminated platelet lysis, and fibrin deposition, ultimately leading to bleeding and necrosis as a consequence of inhibition of fibrin polymerisation by degradation products.

name: dermatitis
description: Inflammation of the skin.

name: stomach, oesophagus and pancreatic intra-epithelial neoplasia
description: stomach, oesophagus and pancreatic intra-epithelial neoplasia

name: adenomatous polyp
description: Benign neoplastic growth containing areas of adenomatous structure (progression).

name: lipomatous tumor
description: Tumors derived from the lipogenic lineage or showing predominantly lipomatous differentiation.

name: medulloblastoma
description: Neoplasm derived from the primitive neurectodermal cells of the cerebellum. (M-9470/3). May be considered by some authorities a synonym of PNET in the CNS.

name: rhabdomyosarcoma
description: Malignant tumor of striated muscle or pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells. (M-8900/3).

name: rhabdomyoma
description: Benign stromal tumors of the soft tissue with skeletal muscle differentiation.

name: rhabdoid sarcoma
description: Sarcomatous tumors, presenting a wide histological, ultrastructural, and immunocytochemical spectrum. M-8963/3.

name: glycogen depletion
description: Reduction in intracellular glycogen content.

name: molar hypercementosis
description: Thickening of the cementum layer of the molars.

name: depletion
description: The removal of accumulated fluids or solids.

name: cystadenocarcinoma
description: Malignant neoplasm derived from glandular epithelium, in which cystic accumulations of retained secretions are formed. (M-8440/3).

name: peripheral nervous system tumors
description: Tumors of the peripheral nervous system.

name: recanalised thrombus
description: An old organized thrombus that has been recanalized to permit blood flow.

name: heterotopia
description: Congenital appearance of a body part or tissue or cell type in a region where it is not normally found ( topographical anomaly).

name: lobular carcinoma
description: A form of breast adenocarcinoma derived from lobular cells. (M-8520/3).

name: scarring alopecia
description: Loss of hair follicles in a diffuse dermal scar.

name: ovarian stromal tumor
description: Tumor consists of a mixture of granulosa, luteal thecal, Sertoli and stromal cells. (M-8590/1).

name: myeloid dysplasias
description: Haematopoietic proliferation with evidence of trilineage dysplasia.

name: cardiovascular developmental defect
description: Abnormal development of the heart or vascular tissue resulting in morphological abnormality.

name: rectal prolapse
description: Eversion through the anus.

name: pathological process
description: The organic response of tissues to external insult, injury or underlying genetic or epigenetic lesion.

name: macrovesicular lipidosis
description: subtype of steatosis with Hepatocytes containing a large well-defined single rounded vacuole within each cell, nucleus and cytoplasm displaced to the periphery,

name: hepatoblastoma
description: Malignant neoplasm of the liver of unknown origin . Liver blastemal cells, neoplastic hepatocytes, oval cells and biliary epithelial cells have been proposed. (M- 8970/3).

name: placental vascular defect
description: Any defect in the maternal or embryonic placental circulation.

name: focal dermatitis
description: locally demarcated region of inflammation in the skin

name: type II hypersensitivity
description: Caused by an antibody/antigen reaction: antibodies are directly or indirectly cytotoxic to antigens on cell surfaces or in connective tissues.

name: endocrine adenoma
description: endocrine adenoma

name: pulmonary embolism
description: Occlusion of pulmonary vessels by an embolus.

name: giant cell tumor of soft tissue
description: Malignant or benign tumor of pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells giving rise to large multinucleated cells (M- 9251/1).

name: epithelial dysplasia
description: epithelial dysplasia

name: myomatous tumor
description: Neoplasms derived from myogenic lineages or predominantly composed of cells showing myomatous differentiation.

name: neurofibromatosis
description: Systemic manifestation of MPATH:435 ( M-9540/1).

name: adenomatous polyposis coli
description: Spontaneous intestinal adenoma formation. Polyps increase in number, causing symptoms of chronic colitis and potentially transform into adenocarcinoma. (M-8220/0).

name: verrucous carcinoma
description: A well-differentiated papillary squamous cell carcinoma. (M-8051/3).

name: hepatic centrolobular fatty metamorphosis
description: Accumulation of clear large vacuoles in hepatocytes (most likely lipid pending frozen sections and oil red O or other lipid stains) around central veins.

name: fusion process defect
description: Failure of two or more structures ( not voids or lumens) to join together.

name: intraductal papillary carcinoma
description: Infiltrating tumor with papillary morphology derived from the breast epithelium (M-8503/3).

name: polyarteritis nodosa
description: Chronic inflammation in and around small and medium sized arteries, often in more than one location.

name: secondary immunodeficiency disease
description: Defect in the immune system subsequent to external injury, infection, ablation or deficiency.

name: biphenotypic leukaemia
description: A leukaemia with at least 90% blasts and differentiation markers of the myeloid and lymphoid lineage.

name: supernumerary structure
description: Additional structure whether normally located or not.

name: papillary cystadenocarcinoma
description: A malignant neoplasm derived from glandular epithelium, in which cysts contain folds or papillary projections into the lumen. (M-8450/3).

name: fatty infiltration
description: Accumulation of mature adipose tissue in a healing wound site or otherwise in response to tissue damage.

name: uterine septic necrosis
description: Necrosis of the uterine wall  with large bacterial colonies on its surface.

name: granular cell tumor
description: granular cell tumor

name: granular cell tumor
description: Large polygonal or round cell tumors with abundant acidophilic cytoplasm containing PAS positive granules. Found especially in the uterine cervix. Aetiology unknown. (M-9580/0).

name: B-cell neoplasms
description: Neoplasm of the B cell lymphoid lineage.

name: follicular dystrophy
description: Degenerative changes in hair follicles resulting in a deformed hair fiber, sometimes root sheath hyperplasia and follicular rupture.

name: dissecting aneurysm
description: Follows the presence of a hematoma in the wall of an artery Splitting of the media occurs, blood enters the split through a tear in the intima.

name: thymoma
description: A neoplasm in the anterior mediastinum, originating from thymic tissue, usually benign, and frequently encapsulated; occasionally invasive, but metastases are rare; histologically, consists of any type of thymic epithelial cell as well as lymphocytes that are usually abundant. (M-8580/1).

name: Burkitt-like lymphoma
description: Highly proliferative mature B-cell lymphoma, poorly defined.

name: myxofibroma
description: A benign neoplasm characterized by mucous and fibroblastic tissues.

name: mesothelial tumor
description: mesothelial tumor

name: air embolism
description: An bubble of air occluding flow through a blood or lymphatic vessel.

name: dermal fibrosis
description: fibrosis in the skin

name: pheochromocytoma
description: A catecholamine-secreting tumor arising from the chromaffin cells of the sympathetic nervous system or adrenal medulla. May be benign or malignant. [See MPATH 398]. (M- 8510/3).

name: infarct
description: An area of necrosis resulting from a sudden cessation of arterial or venous blood supply.

name: anaplastic mammary adenocarcinoma
description: poorly differentiated adenocarcinoma of the mammary gland

name: fibroglandular hyperplasia
description: Benign proliferation of glandular epithelium accompanied by proliferation of fibroblastic stroma.

name: myxoma
description: A benign neoplasm derived from pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells of connective tissue, consisting chiefly of polyhedral and stellate cells that are loosely embedded in a soft mucoid matrix. May show multiple differentiated components. (M-8840/0).

name: empyema
description: Pus in a body cavity; when used without qualification, refers specifically to pyothorax.

name: keratoacanthoma
description: Skin type is thought to arise from follicular epithelium of hair follicles; found in other epithelia. Composed of multiple cup shaped cavities filled with lamellated concentrically arranged or homogeneous cornified masses.

name: bridging necrosis
description: Area of liver necrosis that bridges adjacent portal areas and central veins.

name: tumors of the meninges
description: tumors of the meninges

name: placental site trophoblastic tumor
description: Neoplastic proliferation of intermediate trophoblasts that invades the myometrium at the placental site after a pregnancy. (M-9104/1).

name: pigment dispersion
description: Free pigment in anterior chamber/elsewhere in eye.

name: chronic/recurrent inflammatory disease
description: chronic/recurrent inflammatory disease

name: mucinous cystadenocarcinoma
description: Malignant neoplasm derived from a glandular epithelium, eg. Ovary. Consisting of a solid to cystic mass lined with cuboidal pleomorphic epithelial cells producing a mucinous material. (M- 8470/3).

name: fracture
description: A fracture is the (local) separation of a bone into two, or more, pieces under the action of stress.

name: ulcerative inflammation
description: Combination of inflammation, often suppurative or granulomatous, with ulceration.

name: Myeloproliferation (genetic)
description: Non-reactive persistent accumulation of non-lymphoid haematopoietic cells in the blood which do not infiltrate the spleen and the bone marrow. Genetically determined.

name: cardiac defect
description: Structural, organisational or growth related defects in cardiac development.

name: urelithiasis
description: Formation of urinary concretions in any part of the kidney.

name: subcellular defect
description: Defect of a subcellular structure or organelle.

name: diffuse large B-cell lymphoma, centroblastic type
description: Diffuse follicular centre cell lymphoma mainly composed of centroblasts.

name: precursor T-cell lymphoblastic lymphoma/leukaemia
description: Precursor T cell derived neoplasia. Most commonly found in the thymus.

name: multifocal muscle regeneration
description: multilocular sites of muscle regeneration with centrally located nuclei.

name: tumorlet
description: Small disseminated foci of atypical bronchiolar epithelial hyperplasia. Benign. (M- 8040/1).

name: biliary stasis
description: Cessation of the flow of bile due to bile duct blockage or overproduction.

name: dentinoma
description: Similar lesion to ameloblastic fibroma (MPATH380) , but also showing inductive changes that lead to the formation of dentine (M-9271/0).

name: carcinoma in situ
description: May be used in some systems in preference to its synonyms to indicate lesion specific aprearances. A lesion characterised by changes of the type associated with invasive carcinoma, but physically bounded by the lining epithelium and without local invasion.

name: multifocal bullous emphysema
description: mutilocular bullous emphysema

name: defective growth and differentiation process
description: Abnormal increase or decrease in the rate of cell growth or cell division including associated changes in the differentiation state of adult cells.

name: paragangliomas and glomus tumor
description: Generally benign neoplasms of CHIEF cells arising from neuroectodermal tissues, found in various parts of the body. Note that until recently, glomus tumors were believed to be derived from specialised vascular cells, which is incorrect. Paraganglioma is the preferred term.The nomenclature for pheochromocytoma and paraganglioma is inconsistent. The term paraganglioma is used to refer to any extra-adrenal tumor of the paraganglion system or nonfunctional tumor of the paraganglion system. Functional tumors are referred extra-adrenal pheochromocytoma.

name: fat cell hyperplasia
description: Benign proliferation of adipose tissue.

name: focus of cellular alteration
description: Focal lesions of hepatocytes characterised primarily by altered cytoplasmic tinctorial properties. Classified as basophilic, eosinophilic, clear cell or mixed type.

name: pathological entity
description: Pathological structure or process

name: seborrheic keratosis
description: Superficial, benign, verrucous, often pigmented, greasy lesions consisting of proliferating epidermal cells, resembling basal cells, enclosing cornifying cysts.

name: transitional cell carcinoma in situ
description: Pre-malignant intra-epithelial neoplasm of transitional cells (M-8120/2).

name: glaucoma developmental
description: Consequent on developmental abnormalities in the trabecular network and Schlemm`s canal in the angle.

name: inflammation
description: A tissue reaction to an internal or external injury.

name: granulocytic leukaemia
description: granulocytic leukaemia

name: angiogenesis defect
description: Abnormality in developmental angiogenesis.

name: abnormal organ mass
description: Abnormal mass of organ

name: eccrine gland adenocarcinoma
description: Malignant neoplasm of the eccrine gland (M-8413/3).

name: liquefactive necrosis
description: Soft or fluid tissue remains of a circumscribed area of necrosis digested by proteolytic enzymes.

name: developmental process abnormalities
description: developmental process abnormalities

name: bone marrow granulopoiesis
description: Marked production of granulocytes, primarily neutrophils, usually in response to a major acute inflammatory response.

name: hemangioblastoma
description: A benign neoplasm frequently arising in the cerebellum composed of capillary vessel forming endothelial cells and stromal cells. (M-9161/1).

name: tissue specific degenerative process
description: Degenerative process characteristic of a particular tissue.

name: plasmacytoma
description: Diffuse proliferation of mature plasma cells. Clonal by definition.

name: hypospermia
description: Reduced numbers of sperm.

name: copper deposition
description: Intra and extracellular deposition of copper and copper containing proteins.

name: hepatocholangiocellular carcinoma
description: Malignant tumor of unknown origin showing features of hepatocelluar carcinoma and cholangiocarcinoma. (M-8180/3).

name: ameloblastic fibroma
description: A tumor consisting of proliferating strands and clumps of odontogenic epithelium in a highly cellular fibroblastic stroma resembling the dental papilla of developing teeth. The epithelial component are composed of peripheral cuboidal or cylindrical cells enclosing scant stellate cells. (M-9330/0).

name: adenomyoepithelioma
description: Adenocarcinoma type tumor with both glandular and squamous differentiation. (M-8983/0).

name: serous cystadenoma
description: Ovarian cystadenoma composed of cells similar to tubal epithelium (M-8441/0).

name: osteoblastoma
description: Generally benign osteogenic neoplasm of unknown aetiology. Aggressive form may be confused with osteosarcoma. NOT a syn for osteofibroma. (M-9200/0).

name: hyperplastic polyp
description: A benign polyp, usually in the colon, showing hyperplasia.

name: foreign body acute papillomatous glossitis
description: Papillomatous inflammation of the tongue caused by a foreign body.

name: classical seminoma
description: As MPATH:317, but not spermatocytic (M-9061/3).

name: Abscess
description: A circumscribed collection of purulent exudate frequently associated with swelling and other signs of inflammation.

name: hypergranulosis
description: Increased thickness of the granular layer of a stratified squamous epithelium, associated with hyperorthokeratosis.

name: foreign body aspiration pneumonia
description: Pneumonia caused by aspiration of a foreign body.

name: avulsion
description: Tearing away or separation of two structures or parts.

name: goblet cell metaplasia
description: Metaplasia resulting in formation of mucus secreting goblet cells.

name: nuclear defect
description: Defect in the structure or function of the nuclear membrane or matrix or other component.

name: cellulitis
description: An acute, diffuse, spreading, edematous, suppurative inflammation of the deep subcutaneous tissues and sometimes muscle, which may be associated with abscess formation.

name: fibrin deposition
description: Deposition of fibrin.

name: developmental cystic dysplasia
description: Developmental dysplasia showing epithelial cell bounded cavities.

name: apocrine adenocarcinoma
description: Carcinoma of the glandular epithelium of apocrine glands (M-8401/3).

name: ductal intra-epithelial neoplasia
description: Pre-malignant hyperplastic and/or dysplastic change in the mammary gland epithelium with the potential to give rise to malignant tumors.

name: pseudoxanthoma elasticum
description: Pseudoxanthoma elasticum is a progressive disorder characterized by accumulated deposits of calcium and other minerals in elastic fibers.

name: basal cell tumor
description: Well circumscribed tumor of the basal cells of the epidermis. Rare mitotic figures, benign. (M8147/0).

name: golgi defect
description: Defect in the structure or function of the golgi apparatus.

name: nesidioblastosis
description: Abnormal proliferation of beta cells of developing islets often leading to marked diffuse or focal beta-cell hyperplasia. Considered to generate a potentially cancerous lesion.

name: reactive splenomegaly
description: An increase in the size of the spleen due to ongoing acute or chronic infection.

name: choroid plexus papilloma
description: Benign neoplasm derived from the epithelial cells of the choroid plexus. (M-9390/0).

name: intracellular and extracellular accumulation
description: Accumulation of substances within, on the surface of or between cells.

name: T cell neoplasms character undetermined
description: T cell neoplasms which cannot currently be classified into known subtypes.

name: pre-sacral teratoma
description: Generally benign germ cell derived tumors of male or female containing derivatives from all three germ layers with differentiation in the malignant form being poor. Pre-sacral tumors located in the retrorectal space between the rectum and the sacrococcygeal part of the spine.

name: mucoepidermoid carcinoma
description: Most commonly a salivary gland carcinoma of low grade malignancy composed of mucous, epidermoid, and intermediate cells. (M-8430/3).

name: uric acid deposition
description: Extracellular deposition of uric acid crystals.

name: neuritis
description: Inflammation of a nerve.

name: pineoblastoma
description: Malignant neoplasms which arise from pineoblasts, the primitive pineal stem cells. (M-9362/3).

name: defective branching morphogenesis
description: Defect in the process determining number, angle, pattern or rate of branching of tubular branched structures eg. Glandular ducts.

name: cholecystitis
description: inflammation of the gall bladder

name: embryonal carcinoma
description: Germ cell derived malignant neoplasm of the testis or ovary, composed of anaplastic cells with indistinct cellular borders and large ovoid, round, or bean-shaped nuclei that may have large nucleoli. (M-9070/3 ).

name: ulcer
description: Loss of epithelium and the basement membrane (full thickness). Cf Erosion.

name: micropthalmia
description: Reduced size of the eye globe.

name: granulosa cell tumor
description: . Derived from sex cord stromal cells. In male thought to be Sertoli cells. (M- 8620/1).

name: inter-atrial septal defect
description: Incomplete closure of the inter-atrial septum due to failure of the primary or secondary septum.

name: cartilaginous metaplasia
description: Metaplasia resulting in heterotopic formation of cartilage.

name: pulmonary metastasis
description: Metastatic tumour of unspecified origin in the lung.

name: lymphatic leukaemia
description: lymphatic leukaemia

name: cholelithiasis
description: Presence of concretions in the gallbladder or bile ducts.

name: osseous metaplasia
description: Metaplasia resulting in formation of bone.

name: neurilemmoma
description: neurilemmoma

name: incomplete parenchymal regeneration
description: Incomplete healing usually accompanied by fibrosis.

name: pre-neoplastic lesions
description: Lesions likely to result in progression to frank tumors, which may be classified as pre-neoplastic or pre-cancerous.

name: dermatofibrosarcoma
description: Highly recurrent, infiltrative skin tumors of intermediate malignancy derived from fibroblasts/fibrocytes. Human condition dermatofibrosarcoma protruberans (M-8832/3).

name: autoimmune glomerulonephritis
description: Glomerulonephritis caused by autoimmune attack on the glomerulus.

name: hemangiopericytoma
description: A vascular, usually benign, neoplasm composed of round and spindle cells derived from the pericytes and surround endothelium-lined vessels. (M-9150/0/1/3).

name: lymphatic vessel tumor
description: Neoplasms of the lymphatic vessels.

name: complex tumor
description: Tumors showing multiple histological componants/differentiation.

name: iron deposition
description: Extra- or intra-cellular deposition of iron, iron containing proteins or hemosiderin.

name: osteoporosis
description: Reduction in the quantity of bone or atrophy of skeletal tissue. More severe than MPATH: 53 with gross changes to bone matrix.

name: glandular tumor
description: Neoplasms derived from glandular epithelial cells.

name: adenosquamous carcinoma
description: Mixed adeno- and squamous cell carcinoma. Not yet reported in mice. M-8560/3.

name: sub-retinal hemorrhage
description: Extravascular blood between retina and choroid

name: displacement and deformity
description: Abnormal location, orientation, number, loss or non-specified deformity of a structure or tissue.

name: teratocarcinoma
description: Mixed germ cell neoplasm contaning elements of embryonal carcinoma and teratoma (M-9081/3).

name: Cribriform epididymal hyperplasia
description: The lesion is characterized microscopically by epithelial cells with atypical hyperchromatic nuclei, vacuolization, intratubular lumina formation, infrequent apoptosis, and rare mitotic figures. In contrast to germ cells, the cells of CEH do not express alpha-fetoprotein, carcinoembryonic antigen, or S-100. Ultrastructurally, the cells are pleomorphic with stereocilia at their apical borders and within intratubular lumina, and are supported by a basement membrane. CEH does not appear to be a preneoplastic change.

name: reactive fibrosis
description: Fibrotic reaction to presence of a foreign body.

name: thecoma
description: Derived from sex cord stromal cells, spindle shaped cells arranged in whorls or interlacing bundles. (M- 8600/0).

name: lymphangioma circumscriptum
description: Cutaneous grouped collection of thin-walled translucent vessels, which appear at birth or in early infancy and are commonest around the limb girdles.

name: epidermal inclusion cyst
description: Intradermal or subcutaneous cyst, the wall of which is stratified epithelium containing keratohyalin granules, surrounding a core of debris.

name: gliosis
description: Proliferation of astrocytes in an area of damage in the brain or spinal cord.

name: congestion
description: Presence of an abnormal amount of fluid (but especially of blood) in the vessels or passages of a part or organ.

name: glomus jugulare tumor
description: A glomus tumor arising from the chief cells of the paraganglia ( neurectodermal derivatives) , or glomus bodies, located within the wall (adventitia) of the jugular bulb. (8690/1).

name: arthritis
description: Inflammation of a joint.

name: histiocytic sarcoma
description: Solid tumor mass composed predominantly of histiocytic cells (M-9775/3).

name: histiocytic sarcoma
description: histiocytic sarcoma

name: Sacrococcygeal teratoma
description: Generally benign germ cell derived tumors of male or female containing derivatives from all three germ layers with differentiation in the malignant form being poor. Sacrococcygeal tumors are located at the base of the coccyx.

name: pulmonary blastoma
description: A biphasic tumor containing a primitive epithelial component, that may resemble well-differentiated fetal adenocarcinoma and a primitive mesenchymal stroma, which occasionally has foci of osteosarcoma, chondrosarcoma or rhadomyosarcoma. (M-8972/3).

name: cyst
description: Formation of an epithelium bounded cavity not associated with neoplasia.

name: comedocarcinoma
description: Form of carcinoma of the breast or other organ in which plugs of necrotic malignant cells are present in the ducts. (M -8501/3).

name: renal tubular amyloidosis
description: Pink amorphous material (amyloid) deposited within the renal tubules.

name: hernia
description: Protrusion of a loop or wall of an organ through an abnormal opening.

name: islet cell carcinoma
description: Rare tumor of the islets of Langerhans, most of which produce insulin. (M- 8150/3).

name: cicatricial alopecia
description: Scarring of the hair follicle without affecting the adjacent dermis. Pigment may be associated with fibrous tract in pigmented individuals.

name: mast cell sarcoma
description: Solid tumor mass composed of mast cells.

name: intervertebral disks prolapsed dorsally and ventrally
description: Presence of dorsal and ventrally prolapsed disks in the same vertebral column.

name: extramedullary hemopoiesis
description: The formation of and development of blood cells outside the red pulp of the spleen. Composed of varying numbers of megakaryocytes as well as myeloid and erythroid precursors.

name: myeloid leukaemia
description: Leukaemias of the myeloid lineage.

name: focal hepatic lipidosis
description: Locally circumscribed regions of fatty change.

name: cholangiofibroma
description: Develops from cholangiofibrosis, fibrosis of the biliary ducts and is only potentially malignant.

name: labyrinth zone defect
description: Defect in size, cellular composition, function or organisation of the labyrinthine zone of the placenta.

name: chronic dermatitis
description: chronic inflammation of the skin

name: type I hypersensitivity
description: This is manifested by localized or generalized reaction that occurs immediately (minutes) after exposure to an antigen to which the person/animal was previously sensitized. It is IgE-mediated, and mast cell activation and degranulation are hallmarks.

name: endocrine adenocarcinoma
description: obsolete.

name: fat embolism
description: Occlusion of vessels caused by entry of lipid or fatty cells into the circulation. Usually following trauma.

name: intra-epithelial neoplasia
description: Non-invasive changes characterized by alteration in the size, shape and organization of the cellular components of an epithelial tissue. Do not confuse with developmental dysplasia MPATH:64.

name: lymphangiosarcoma
description: A malignant neoplasm derived from vascular tissue in which the neoplastic cells originate from the endothelial cells of lymphatic vessels. (M-9170/3).

name: neurofibroma
description: Peripheral nerve tumor consisting of chaotic arrays of wavy schwann cell bundles and fibroblasts interspersed within a matrix rich in collagen and mucopolysaccharide. (M9540/0).

name: adenoma
description: A benign epithelial neoplasm in which the tumor cells may form glands or glandlike structures. In different instances this may remain a benign tumor or progress to malignancy.

name: squamous cell papilloma
description: A benign tumor consisting of villous or arborescent outgrowths of fibrovascular stroma covered by neoplastic squamous epithelial cells.

name: intervertebral disk prolapse
description: Rupture of the intervertebral disc, usually dorsally to compress the spinal cord, secondary to trauma.

name: fibrinoid necrosis
description: Necrosis in which the necrotic tissue shows deeply eosinophilic staining similar to that of fibrin.

name: fistula
description: An abnormal passage between two internal organs or leading from a cavity to the body surface.

name: intraductal carcinoma
description: In situ carcinoma of the mammary ductal epithelium. (M- 8500/2).

name: pulmonary interstitial mineralisation
description: Small foci of mineralization within the interstitium between alveoli.

name: immunodeficiency - myeloid/phagocytic defect
description: Primary defect in the myeloid arm of the immune system.

name: monocytic leukaemia
description: Leukaemia in which neoplastic cells are poorly or moderately differentiated with a monocytic but no neutrophilic component. At least 20% of the cells must be blasts.

name: septation defect
description: Any defect in the formation of septae not describable as perforation.

name: papillary adenoma
description: A benign neoplasm derived from a glandular epithelium, in which solid tumors show papillary structures projecting onto fibrovascular stroma. (M-8260/0).

name: fibro-osseous lesion
description: Lesion of bone showing accelerated osteoclastic bone resorption coupled with fibroplasia. Later stages show proliferation of osteoblasts.

name: septic necrosis
description: Necrosis associated with or caused by local bacterial infection.

name: Non-Lymphoid neoplasias
description: Hematological neoplasias of non-lymphoid origin.

name: hypoplastic ventricle
description: Reduction in cell number of one or both of the two lower chambers of the heart.

name: classic Burkitt lymphoma
description: Highly proliferative B-cell lymphoma characteristically seen in c-Myc transgenic mice, derived from mature B cells.

name: hypoplastic gut associated lymphoid tissue
description: Reduced mass of GALT resulting form fewer cells.

name: mesonephric tumor
description: Tumor beleived to be derived from mesonephric remnants. (M-8310/3).

name: embolus
description: A plug formed from a variety of materials occluding a vessel or tube.

name: acute septic inflammation
description: acute inflammation due to infection.

name: neuroblastoma
description: A malignant neoplasm characterized by immature, poorly differentiated nerve cells of embryonic type. (M-9500/3).

name: granulomatous epicarditis
description: A mixed inflammatory cell infiltrate, primarily macrophages and some syncitial cells, around the heart attached to the epicardium.

name: purpura
description: Purple and variously colored lesions caused by extensive haemorrhage into the skin through ecchymoses/petechia.

name: effacing granuloma
description: Replacement of normal tissue by granuloma.

name: chondroblastoma
description: A benign or malignant neoplasm occuring in the epiphyses of long bones, consisting of highly cellular tissue resembling embryonic cartilage. (M-9230/0, /3).

name: fibroepithelial polyp
description: A polypoid outgrowth of both epidermis and dermal fibrovascular tissue.

name: angiomyxoma
description: Angiomyxoma is a poorly circumscribed, slowly growing lesion composed of spindle-shaped and stellate cells evenly distributed in an abundant myxoid matrix. The lesion contains numerous vessels, often showing some hyalinization of their walls, and occasionally surrounded by a few smooth muscle cells. Immunohistochemically, tumor cells may express desmin and/ or smooth muscle actin (M-8841/1).

name: abscess
description: A circumscribed collection of purulent exudate frequently associated with swelling and other signs of inflammation.

name: squamous hyperplasia
description: Benign proliferation of epidermal cells with hyperkeratosis. Variable growth pattern, regular to papillary (exophytic squamous cell hyperplasia).

name: inverted squamous papilloma
description: A benign tumor consisting of villous or arborescent outgrowths of fibrovascular stroma covered by neoplastic epithelial cells in which proliferating epithelium is invaginated beneath the surface and is more smoothly rounded. (M-8053/0).

name: necrosis
description: Morpholological changes after intravital (Pathologic) death of one or more cells, or of a portion of tissue or organ, resulting from irreversible damage;characterised by mitochondrial swelling, nuclear pyknosis, karyolysis, swollen and abnormally pale basophilic staining; or karyorrhexis, rupture and fragmentation of the nucleus. Energy independent cf. Apoptosis MPATH 3.

name: hydatidiform mole
description: Vesicular or cystic tumor with hydropic villi resulting from the proliferation of trophoblast in the absence ( complete) or the presence ( partial) of an embryo. Most complete moles are homozygous androgenetic XX 46.(M-9100/0).

name: pulmonary adenomatosis
description: Neoplastic proliferation of cuboidal cells lining alveoli most likely type II pneumocytes.

name: medullary carcinoma
description: Derived from calcitonin-producing cells (thyroid). In humans a type of carcinoma composed of epithelial elements with considerable lymphoid stroma (breast). Not yet reported in mice. (M-8510/3).

name: symmetry defect
description: Any aberration of the normal symmetrical organisation of the body pattern.

name: sialocele
description: Salivary gland duct occlusion resulting in massive enlargement forming a large cyst-like structure.

name: necrotic inflammation
description: Acute inflammatory reaction in which the predominant histological change is rapid diffuse necrosis throughout the affected tissue.

name: myeloid proliferations (non-reactive)
description: Non-reactive persistent accumulation of non-lymphoid haematopoietic cells. Genetically determined.

name: arteriovenous anastomosis
description: Formation of vessels between arterioles and venules bypassing capillary circulation.

name: spermatocoele
description: A spermatocoele is a cyst that contains spermatozoa. .

name: sebaceous adenocarcinoma
description: Malignant neoplasm of the sebaceous cells - rare areas of differentiation, severe nuclear atypia (M-8410/3).

name: myxoid/myxomatous degeneration
description: A conversion of the connective tissues into a gelatinous or mucous substance.

name: Diffuse large B-cell lymphoma
description: Diffuse proliferation of large B lymphoid cells.

name: trichogranuloma
description: Dermal granuloma surrounding hair fibers.

name: cataract
description: Opacity of the lens.

name: precursor T-cell neoplasms
description: Neoplasms of precursor T cells.

name: regeneration
description: repair, reproduction, or replacement of lost or injured cells, tissues, or organs.

name: small cell carcinoma
description: Neuroendocrine cell derived anaplastic carcinoma composed of small cells, usually of the lung producing a variety of peptide hormones. (M-8041/3). 1.2.3.4 of MMHCC classification.

name: carcinoma
description: Any of various types of malignant neoplasm derived from epithelial cells, chiefly glandular (adenocarcinoma) or squamous (squamous cell carcinoma).

name: stasis
description: Cessation of movement of a body fluid or liquid.

name: cementoma
description: Reactive fibro-osseous lesion derived from odotongenic cells in the periodontal ligament (M-9272/0).

name: moderate intra-epithelial epithelial neoplasia
description: Moderate non-invasive changes in cell morphology and tissue architecture confined to the epithelium alone.

name: bullous emphysema
description: Rupture of alveolar walls result in large rounded open air spaces in the lung

name: gonadal tumor
description: Germ cell and non-germ cell tumors of the testis and ovary.

name: pathological anatomical entity
description: Anatomically located instance of pathological response or entity.

name: osteosarcoma
description: Malignant neoplasm derived form mesenchymal stem cells, osteoblasts or osteocytes. Highly invasive and destructive tumor rising in the skeleton with osteoid and immature woven bone. (M-9180/3).

name: myoepithelial hyperplasia
description: Benign proliferation of glandular myoepithelial cells.

name: intussception
description: Condition in which a part of the intestine has invaginated into another section of intestine,

name: hyperostosis
description: Hypertrophy of bone characterised by an abnormal increase in non-neoplastic skeletal bone mass. These may be proliferative or non-proliferative lesions.

name: pseudoepithelioma/pseudocarcinoma
description: Benign hyperplasia and down-growth of epidermal cells. Microscopically resembling well-differentiated squamous cell carcinoma.

name: transitional cell carcinoma
description: Malignant neoplasm of transitional cells (M-8120/3).

name: cavernous hemangioma
description: Deep cutaneous hemangioma with large dilated vascular spaces that manifests spontaneous involution.

name: cataract; lens extrusion
description: Involves capsular rupture usually of the posterior lens capsule, close to birth or in the first few weeks postpartum. Cortical material spills into the vitreous humor and may be disseminated through the eye.

name: failed transfer of maternal immunoglobulin
description: Defect in the immune system subsequent to failure to attain passive immunity from maternal transfer of immunoglobulins.

name: abnormal organ length
description: Abnormality of extent of the normal long axis

name: choristoma
description: Similar to hamartoma, including the mass lesion requirement, but unlike hamartoma, includes heterotopic tissue of an adult or embryonic nature ( topographical and developmental anomaly).

name: clear cell hidradenoma
description: Tumor derived from eccrine sweat glands composed of clear glycogen rich cells. ( M-84020 ).

name: hemorrhagic necrosis
description: Necrosis associated with local hemorrhage.

name: follicular atresia
description: Degeneration and resorption of an ovarian follicle before it reaches maturity and ruptures.

name: angiokeratoma
description: An intradermal capillary telangiectasis with hyperkeratosis and acanthosis (M-9141/0).

name: plasma membrane defect
description: Defect in the structure or function of the plasma membrane.

name: B-natural killer cell lymphoma
description: Unusual lymphoma type described in thymectomised (SL/Kh x AKR/Ms) F1 mice. No equivalent found in human to date. See reference for detailed phenotype.

name: alveolar rhabdomyosarcoma
description: Malignant tumor of striated muscle or pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells composed mainly of small round cells, with some partial skeletal muscle differentiation.

name: spermatogenesis defect
description: Compromise or abnormality of the process of spermatogenesis

name: ceroid deposition
description: Intracellular deposition of golden or yellow-brown pigment, acid fast and insoluble in lipid solvents. Believed to be a type of lipofuscin.

name: hepatocholangiocellular adenoma
description: Benign tumor of unknown origin showing features of hepatocelluar adenoma and cholangioma.

name: aberrant crypt foci
description: Sensu gastrointsestinal tract. visible microscopically in whole mount colonic tissue. One or more crypts larger than most, have a thickened layer of epithelial cells that stain more intensely with methylene blue. Some have a slit shaped luminal opening, and increased pericryptal space and are elevated from the focal plane of the microscope. ACF is not a histologic diagnosis.

name: auricular deformation
description: acquired dysmorphology of the external pinna following trauma or infection.

name: serous adenocarcinoma
description: Adenocarcinoma from a serous gland producing and containing serous proteinaceous secretions (M-8441/3).

name: chondrosarcoma
description: Malignant neoplasm derived form pluripotential mesenchymal cells, chondrocytes or chondroblasts. No production of osteoid. (M-9220/3).

name: otitis externa
description: Inflammation of the outer ear.

name: seminoma
description: Tumor derived from spermatogenic cells resembling spermatogenia or spermatocytes. NOS ( M9061/3).

name: glossitis
description: Acute or chronic inflammation of the tongue.

name: basal cell hyperplasia
description: Benign proliferation of the basal layer cells of the skin.

name: pneumonia
description: An inflammatory condition of the lung, especially affecting the alveoli, associated with fever, chest symptoms, and congestion.

name: involution
description: Turning in of the edges of a structure.

name: glandular metaplasia
description: Development of heterotopic glandular epithelia.

name: bursal cyst
description: A retention cyst, resulting from an obstruction to the duct of a gland, within a bursa.

name: extracellular matrix deposition
description: Abnormal deposition of extracellular matrix proteins or other components.

name: Dorsal/ventral axis defect
description: Dorsoventral aberration of the normal symmetrical organisation of the body pattern.

name: trichoepithelioma
description: Multiple small benign nodules derived from basal cells of hair follicles enclosing small cornified cell containing cysts. (M-8100/0).

name: myeloid leukaemia with maturation
description: Leukaemia in which neoplastic cells are moderately differentiated with a neutrophilic but not monocytic component. At least 20% of the cells have to be blasts.

name: lymph node reticuloendothelial cell hyperplasia
description: Proliferation of the reticuloendothelial cells in the medulla of the lymph node.

name: glaucoma
description: Increase in the intraocular pressure.

name: choroid plexus carcinoma
description: Malignant neoplasm derived from the epithelial cells of the choroid plexus. (M-9390/3).

name: mesodermal mixed tumor
description: Neoplasm showing multiple phases, derived from mesoderm (M-8951/3).

name: protein deposition
description: Non-specified intra or extracellular deposition of protein.

name: Clara cell adenoma
description: Benign tumor of the Clara cells of the bronchioalveolar epithelium.

name: aplasia
description: Absence of an organ or tissue coupled with persistence of the organ/tissue primordium, which fails to develop completely.

name: tumors of neurepithelial tissue
description: Tumors of neuronal and non-neuronal cells derived from embryonic neurepithelium.

name: trichoblastoma
description: Basaloid neoplasm with frequent primitive hair follicles.

name: kyphosis
description: Abnormality of the kyphotic curvature of the spine.

name: fibrothecoma
description: obsolete use thecoma MPATH:334.

name: metaplasia
description: Abnormal transformation of an fully differentiated adult cell or tissue of one kind into a differentiated tissue of another kind. An adult instance of developmental transdifferentiation MPATH:85 Traditionally defined as a form of abnormal regeneration in which a type of cell different from that found normally in a given location is produced.

name: metastatic tumor
description: metastatic tumour of unspecified origin

name: Hepatocytomegaly
description: Increase in size of hepatocytes characterised by organelle hyperplasia and enlarged cellular volume.

name: myeloid metaplasia
description: A progressive disease of the bone marrow where neoplastic bone marrow stem cells lodge and grow at sites outside the bone marrow.

name: complete parenchymal regeneration
description: Complete healing through parenchymal regeneration - no fibrosis.

name: decidual defect
description: Any defect in the formation, architecture, cellular composition or function of the maternal decidua.

name: chordoma
description: Believed to arise from primitive notochord remnants . Usually occurs along the axial skeleton and is characterised by the presence of bubble cells containing large unstained cytoplasmic vacuoles with central or eccentricc nuclei. Benign but locally invasive. (M-9370/3).

name: immune mediated thrombocytopenia
description: A condition resulting from an increased rate of immune mediated platelet destruction.

name: membraneoproliferative glomerulonephritis
description: A chronic glomerulonephritis characterized by mesangial cell proliferation, increased lobular separation of glomeruli, thickening of glomerular capillary walls and increased mesangial matrix,.

name: hemangioma
description: Neoplasm derived from endothelial cells. May be of capillary or cavernous type with large vascular channels. (M-9130/0 + M-9120/0 respectively).

name: liposarcoma
description: Malignant neoplasms which probably originate in primitive mesenchymal stem cell populations differentiating down a lipomatous pathway. (M-8850/3).

name: sub-ependymoma
description: Neoplasm derived from sub-ependymal astrocytes (M-9383/1).

name: hyalinosis
description: Intracellular deposition of eosinophilic material.

name: fibroadenoma
description: A benign neoplasm derived from glandular epithelium, in which there is a abundant stroma of proliferating fibroblasts and connective tissue. (M-9010/0).

name: osteopenia
description: Reduced bone mass due to inadequate synthesis of osteoid, resulting in decreased calcification.

name: cribriform adenocarcinoma
description: Tumor composed of sheets or nests of cells forming lumens with round, punched out spaces.

name: dilatation
description: Increase in the diameter of an orifice or tubular structure beyond its normal dimensions.

name: follicular adenoma
description: Adenoma derived from the follicular cells of the thyroid follicles. Follicular, paipillary and solid forms. M- 8330/0.

name: inverted transitional cell papilloma
description: Pre-malignant lesion of transitional cells, papillomatous form, in which proliferating epithelium is invaginated beneath the surface.

name: struma ovarii
description: Rare ovarian tumor, regarded as monodermal teratoma, in which thyroid tissue has surpassed the other elements; occasionally associated with hyperthyroidism (M-9090/0).

name: malposition
description: Abnormal position or orientation of a structure insufficient to be called a heterotopia.

name: polycystic disease
description: A group of degenerative disorders resulting in multiple cysts in tissues.

name: foreign body gingivitis
description: inflammation of the tooth gum caused by a foreign body.

name: cystic hygroma
description: Variant of cavernous lymphangioma (MPATH:804) showing gross dilatation of lymphatic channels.

name: osteoid deposition
description: Deposition of organic bone matrix.

name: fibrosis
description: Reactive formation of fibrous tissue.

name: melanoma
description: Tumor of neurectodermal origin, usually melanocytes, showing dense deposition of melanin granules, although amelanotic melanomas have been reported. (M-8720/3).

name: fluid accumulation
description: Abnormal accumulation of fluid; blood or lymph.

name: carotid body tumor
description: Paraganglioma arising in the CHIEF cells of the carotid body (M-8692/1).

name: immune mediated disease
description: Tissue response to inappropriate immune/inflammatory process.

name: hemorrhage and non-specified extravasation
description: Abnormal release of whole blood or the cellular component from the circulation.

name: leiomyosarcoma
description: Malignant tumor derived form pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells or smooth muscle cells. (M- 8890/3).

name: nephroblastoma
description: Embryonal tumor thought to be derived from metanephric blastema. Mono, bi or triphasic, sometimes with heterotypic differentiation. (M-8960/3).

name: synovial-like tumor
description: Neoplasms of synovial origin.

name: mucometra
description: A uterus distended with a fluid containing large quantities of mucin.

name: curvature defect
description: Inappropriate curvature of a structure.

name: clear cell adenocarcinoma
description: An adenocarcinoma characterised by the presence of varying combinations of clear and hobnail-shaped tumor cells. (M-8310/3).

name: cartilagenous erosion
description: Fragmentation and erosion of articular cartilage.

name: hamartoma
description: A focal malformation resembling a neoplasm which results from faulty development of an organ; composed of an abnormal mixture of tissue elements, or an abnormal proportion of a single element. Growth and location are usually normal for that tissue cf. Heterotopia/Choristoma MPATH:76/MPATH:477.

name: islet cell adenoma
description: Usually pancreatic B cell derived tumors mostly producing insulin. (M- 8150/0).

name: desmoplasia
description: Connective tissue proliferative reaction induced by a neoplastic process.

name: pseudocyesis
description: Appearance of clinical and/or subclinical signs and symptoms associated with pregnancy when the animal is not pregnant

name: intervertebral disk prolapse dorsal
description: Dorsal prolapse of the intervertebral disk.

name: germ cell defect
description: Abnormal morphology, differentiation or location of primordial germ cells or their descendents. Not neoplastic.

name: cystic hyperplasia
description: Formation of multiple retention cysts from obstruction of ducts or glands by hyperplasia of the lining epithelium.

name: myelodysplastic disorder
description: Haematopoietic proliferation with evidence of trilineage dysplasia. Less than 20% should be blasts.

name: Mature B-cell neoplasms
description: Lymphomas originating in peripheral B cells.

name: epidermolysis bullosa lesions
description: Lesions of a connective tissue disease causing blisters in the skin and mucosal membranes.

name: cholangiocarcinoma
description: Malignant tumor derived from the bile duct epithelium. (M8160/3).

name: glycogen cell defect
description: Lack of, displacement of, or abnormality in function or growth of the glycogen cells.

name: granulomatous dermatitis
description: granulomatous inflammation of the skin

name: carcinoid tumor
description: Carcinoid tumors are of neuroendocrine origin and derived from primitive stem cells.
