Found predominantly in the lung and gut they are capable of secreting a large range of substances and have a number of histological subtypes. May resemble but are distinct from small cell lung carcinoma in the lung. (M-8240/3).

name: bone marrow embolism
description: Occlusion of vessels caused by entry of bone marrow, often fatty debris into the circulation. Usually following trauma.

name: anaplastic hepatocellular carcinoma
description: anaplastic carcinoma of the liver.

name: atrophy
description: A reduction in size of organs or tissues as a result of cell death, loss of cellularity of whatever cause, reduced cellular proliferation or decreased cellular volume.

name: lymphangiomyomatosis
description: Characterized by benign peribronchial, perivascular, and perilymphatic proliferation of atypical smooth muscle resulting in vascular and airway obstruction, cyst formation, and a progressive decline in lung function. (M- 9174/1).

name: squamous cell carcinoma in situ
description: Pre-neoplastic intraepithelial lesion of squamous cells (M-8070/2).

name: splenomegaly
description: An increase in size of the spleen.

name: fat necrosis
description: Dead and dying adipose tissue, characterized by the formation of small gray or white foci of soapy (saponified) cellular debris.

name: infiltrating duct carcinoma
description: Derived from the mammary ductal epithelium and penetrating the stroma (M-8500/3).

name: splenic hemosiderosis
description: Spleen contains foci of macrophages containing yellow brown pigment that is positive for iron using Prussian blue.

name: immunodeficiency - lymphoid defect
description: Primary defect in the lymphoid arm of the immune system.

name: myelomonocytic leukaemia
description: Leukaemia in which neoplastic cells are moderately differentiated with a neutrophilic and a monocytic component. At least 20% of the cells have to be blasts.

name: persistent embryonic structure
description: Persistence of an embryonic structure or tissue into the post-natal period in its normal location; (Chronological/temporal anomaly).

name: papillary adenocarcinoma
description: A malignant neoplasm derived from a glandular epithelium, in which solid tumors show papillary structures projecting onto fibrovascular stroma. (M-8260/3).

name: Meckel's diverticulum
description: A Meckel's diverticulum is a pouch on the wall of the lower part of the intestine that is present at birth.

name: hypertrophic ventricle
description: Thickening of the wall of one or both of the heart ventricles.

name: primary mediastinal (thymic) diffuse large B cell lymphoma
description: Primary B-cell lymphoma of the thymus. Reported in C57BL/6 mice infected with replication defective MuLV. Not clear that this is the equivalent of the human disease.

name: hypoplastic tissue
description: Tissue showing smaller mass as a consequence of deficient proliferation or premature differentiation.

name: mesonephroma
description: Benign or malignant neoplasm of the ovary and corpus uteri, thought to originate in mesonephric structures. (M-9110/3).

name: ovarian tubulostromal tumor
description: non-malignant neoplasia of the ovary.

name: ganglioneuroma
description: A benign neoplasm composed of mature ganglionic neurons scattered singly or in clumps within a relatively abundant and dense stroma of neurofibrils and collagenous fibers. (M-9490/0).

name: petechia
description: Small hemorrhagic spots in the skin caused by blood vessel breakdown.

name: granuloma
description: Collection of epithelioid macrophages into a nodule

name: osseous and chondromatous tumor
description: Neoplasms of bone and cartilage.

name: epithelial and stromal hyperplasia
description: Abnormal proliferation of epithelial and stromal cells.

name: healing and repair structure
description: Physical entity or structure associated with normal or abnormal tissue healing or repair following extrinsic or intrinsic damage.

name: mesothelial hyperplasia
description: Benign proliferation of mesothelial cells lining body cavities presenting as small solid cell clusters or multiple layers with columnar morphology and delicate eosinophilic cytoplasm.

name: squamous cell tumor
description: Neoplasms of stratified squamous epithelial cells.

name: apoptosis
description: Energy dependent cell death induced by intrinsic genetic or developmental programme, or external stimuli such as addition or withdrawal of cytokines or trophic factors, radiation, chemotherapeutic agents etc. Characterised by cell shrinkage, increases in membrane permeability, endonucleolyis and nuclear fragmentation resulting in the formation of rapidly endocytosed apoptotic bodies.

name: choriocarcinoma
description: Tumor derived from malignant trophoblastic cells. May be found in the uterus, ovary and testis. May also be derived from teratomas and teratocarcinomas in males. (M-9100/3).

name: immunodeficiency disease
description: Defective immune response; can be primary due to defect in immune system or secondary/acquired due to disease.

name: lobular carcinoma in situ
description: Non-infiltrating form of lobular adenocarcinoma derived from the ductal epithelium. (M-8520/2).

name: ependymoma malignant
description: ependymoma malignant

name: pseudocyst
description: Formation of extracellular (sensu pancreas) non-epithelial bounded spaces containing accumulated products or substances.

name: thyroid follicle pleomorphism
description: Thyroid gland follicles are filled with colloid but vary greatly in size.

name: granulomatous inflammation
description: Nodular inflammatory reaction, containing compactly grouped epithelioid cells, giant cells, and other macrophages. The basic inflammatory unit is termed a granuloma.

name: aneurysm
description: Localised dilation of an artery or heart chamber usually due to an acquired or congenital weakness of the wall of the artery or chamber.

name: compression
description: Exertion of abnormal force on a structure or structures usually resulting in deformation and damage.

name: papillary hidradenoma
description: Benign apocrine sweat gland tumor (8405/0).

name: general degenerative process
description: Change of tissue to a lower state of integrity or less functional form, as in heart failure.

name: follicular B cell lymphoma
description: A lymphoid proliferation composed of a mixture of centroblasts and centrocytes that may or may not have a nodular(follicular)pattern. The follicular dendritic cell network is not present, unlike in the human. The equivalent typical translocation (Chr. 14:18 )seen in humans has not been reported in the mouse.

name: testicular torsion
description: The testicle twisted around the vascular tract to constrict flow resulting in liquifactive necrosis of the affected testicle.

name: atherosclerosis
description: Characterised by irregular lipid deposits in the wall of arteries, causing narrowing of their lumens and proceeding eventually to fibrosis and calcification.

name: T-cell neoplasms
description: Neoplasms derived from cells of the T lymphocyte lineage.

name: primitive neurectodermal tumor
description: Primitive neuroectodermal tumors (PNET) are neoplasms derived from primitive neural stem cells either in the CNS or the periphery . These are small-cell, malignant embryonal tumors showing divergent differentiation of variable degree along neuronal, glial, or rarely mesenchymal lines. (M-9473/3, M-9364/3).

name: papillary transitional cell carcinoma
description: A generally malignant neoplasm consisting of villous or arborescent outgrowths of fibrovascular stroma covered by atypical neoplastic epithelial or urothelial cells cells.

name: coccygeal hemivertebrae
description: abnormally shaped vertebral body often triangular as opposed to rectangular.

name: cementoblastoma
description: A neoplasm arising from the periodontal ligament (M-9273/0).

name: mild intra-epithelial neoplasia
description: Mild non-invasive changes in cell morphology and tissue architecture confined to the epithelium alone.

name: Splendore-Hoeppli phenomenon
description: In vivo formation of intensely eosinophilic material (radiate, star-like, asteroid or club-shaped configurations) around microorganisms (fungi, bacteria and parasites) or biologically inert substances.

name: thyroid C-cell carcinoma
description: Malignant neoplasm derived from the calcitonin producing C-cells of the thyroid gland. (M-8510/3, M-8345/3).

name: hyperplastic tissue
description: An organ or a tissue with an abnormal increase in the number of cells as a consequence of cell proliferation.

name: osteoma
description: Benign neoplasm derived from osteoblasts or osteocytes composed of very dense bone with predominantly woven structure. ( M-9180/0).

name: microglandular hyperplasia
description: Benign proliferation of glandular epithelia, eg. Endocervical glands. Consists of tightly packed glandular or tubular units, which vary in size, lined by a flattened-to-cuboidal epithelium.

name: uterine ectasia
description: Dilation of the uterus

name: cardiomyopathy
description: A disease of the heart muscle or myocardium proper.

name: parakeratosis
description: Thickening of the surface cell layer of a stratified squamous epithelium with retention of nuclei in the cells of the stratum corneum.

name: transitional cell tumor
description: Neoplasms of transitional epithelia, eg kidney, ureter , bladder , cervix.

name: pyogenic granuloma
description: A small rounded mass of inflamed, highly vascular granulation tissue on the skin, frequently having an ulcerated surface. More likely a true neoplasm rather than a reactive lesion.

name: nephrogenic metaplasia
description: .A rare benign neoplasm of the mucosa of the urinary bladder or the urethra, consisting of tubular structures resembling those of the nephron.

name: cataract; cortical liquefactive
description: Of developmental origins; nucleus and cortex become completely liquefied in post-natal life.

name: acquired immunodeficiency
description: Defect in the immune system subsequent to external injury, infection or ablation.

name: telangiectasia
description: A lesion formed by a dilated capillary or terminal artery.

name: abnormal organ size
description: Abnormal organ dimensions or weight

name: ceruminous adenoma
description: Benign adenomatous neoplasia of the ceruminous glands of the external auditory meatus (M-8420/0).

name: gangrene
description: Extensive necrosis from whatever cause, often following chronic ischemia.

name: B6 dermatitis
description: Follicular dystrophy, rupture, foreign body reaction, ulceration, scarring, pseudoepitheliomatous hyperplasia are part of a syndrome commonly called B6 dermatitis in black strains of mice.

name: angiofibroma
description: .A benign neoplasm of fibrous tissue in which there are multiple large and small dilated vascular channels ( M9160/0).

name: peroxysomal defect
description: Defect in the structure or function of the peroxysomes.

name: Plasma cell neoplasms
description: Diffuse proliferation of mature plasma cells. Clonal by definition. Includes the equivalent of human myeloma (ICD-O 9732/3).

name: pyelectasia
description: Distension of the renal pelvis by accumulated fluid or urine.

name: aspermia
description: Lack of sperm.

name: glioma
description: Neoplasm derived from astrocytes and oligodendrocytes. (M-9380/3, M-9440/3).

name: calcium deposition
description: Intra or extracellular deposition of calcium usually as calcium phosphate.

name: cholangioma
description: Benign neoplasm of the biliary duct. Occurs in solid and cystic forms. (M-8160/0).

name: demyelination
description: Reduction of myelin content in neuronal sheath.

name: potentially cancerous lesions
description: Lesions which in some cases have the potential to become progressively growing malignant tumors.

name: post-traumatic structural abnormality
description: Morphological abnormality following trauma or related insult such as infection.

name: pseudomyxoma peritonei
description: Tumor characterized by extensive spread of a mucin-secreting neoplasm along the peritoneal surfaces (M-8480/6).

name: chondroma
description: A benign neoplasm derived from mesodermal cells that form cartilage composed of well differentiated hyaline cartilage (M-9220/0).

name: focal ulcerative dermatitis
description: circumscribed ulceration of the skin penetrating the basement membrane as part of  inflammation process.

name: mixed germ cell tumor
description: Malignant neoplasm of the testis/ovary including various elements of germ cell tumors (M-9085/3).

name: angiectasia
description: Dilatation of a blood vessel or valve.

name: actinic keratosis
description: Discrete, flat or elevated, verrucous, keratotic lesions. Epidermal changes are characterized by acanthosis, parakeratosis, and dyskeratoses. Dysplastic change is present and the keratinocytes vary in size and shape. Associated with UV exposure in humans. Not defined in mice to date.

name: luteal cell tumor
description: Tumor derived from sex cords composed of highly luteinised cells with extensive pale granular cytoplasm. (M- 8610/0).

name: synechia
description: An adhesion, usually between the iris and the cornea or the lens capsule.

name: gastric metaplasia
description: Appearance of heterotopic gastric epithelium.

name: steatitis
description: Inflammation of fatty tissue.

name: angiogenesis
description: Aberrant process of blood vessel formation and the subsequent remodeling process; does not refer to the initial establishment of the vascular network by vasculogenesis.

name: anterior/posterior axis defect
description: Anteroposterior aberration of the normal symmetrical organisation of the body pattern.

name: hyperplastic nodule
description: Expansion of small hyperplastic lesions to become macroscopically nodules, compressing adjacent cells.

name: syringoma
description: A benign, often multiple, sometimes eruptive neoplasm of the sweat gland ducts composed of very small round cysts. (M-8407/0).

name: fibrous histiocytoma
description: Benign or maligant tumor derived from pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells showing fibrous and histiocytic differentiation (M-8830/0).

name: developmental hypoplasia
description: Underdevelopment of an organ due to a decrease in the number of cells through failure to proliferate leading to lack of development.

name: myeloid leukaemia without maturation
description: Leukaemia in which neoplastic cells are poorly differentiated and not monocytic. At least 90% of the cells have to be blasts.

name: cartilagenous embolism
description: Occlusion of a vessel by a piece of dissected cartilage.

name: astrocytoma
description: Glioma derived from astrocytes, both benign and malignant forms (M-9400/3).

name: emphysema
description: Abnormal accumulation of air in the interstitial connective tissue of a structure. Sensu Lung: Pulmonary emphysema; characterised by abnormal increase in the size of air (alveolar) spaces distal to the terminal bronchiole with degenerative changes in their walls and reduction in their number.

name: craniopharyngioma
description: A benign or malignant neoplasm, which may be cystic, developing from the epithelium of Rathke`s pouch and occuring with or close to the pituitary gland. (M-9350/1).

name: melanin deposition
description: Intra or extracellular deposition of melanin.

name: agenesis
description: Failure of a tissue or organ to develop.

name: glioblastoma
description: Develop primarily through increasing anaplasia of well differentiated gliomas, mainly astrocytomas or oligodendrogliomas. Typically large and contain cells of different sizes with irrregular nuclei and atypical mitotic figures. (M-9440/3).

name: dermoid cyst
description: Cystic ovarian teratomas with different mature cell types (M-9084/3).

name: spiradenoma
description: Cellular neoplasm with well formed palisades of basaloid cells adjacent to less basophilic smaller cells with occasional central deposition of amorphous eosinophilic material. These tumors share some features with cylindroma type tumors but have a less well developed jigsaw puzzle-like architecture and tend to be more cellular.

name: spinal structural defects
description: Structural defects of the bony and muscular components of the vertebrae.

name: androblastoma
description: obsolete use Sertoli cell tumor MPATH: 331.

name: histiocytic pneumonitis
description: Pneumonitis involving subpleural histiocytosis.

name: erythroid leukaemia
description: Leukaemia with at least 50% of nucleated erythroid cells infiltrating haematopoietic tissue.

name: degenerative entity
description: degenerative entity

name: hypertrophic tissue
description: Tissue or cells undergoing hypertrophy, MPATH: 159.

name: nuchal edema
description: Edema of the posterior aspect of the fetal neck caused by an accumulation of fluid, usually lymph.

name: transitional cell metaplasia
description: Metaplastic response of the transitional epithelium, for example in the bladder to give squamous metaplasia and glandular metaplasia for example.

name: crystalloid formation
description: Accumulation of chitinase-like protein.

name: parenchymal regeneration
description: Post-injury regeneration of the functional tissue parenchyma. Eg. Liver.

name: soft tissue tumor
description: Neoplasms of the soft and connective tissues.

name: immune mediated hemolytic anaemia
description: An anemic/erythrocytopenic condition resulting from an increased rate of immune mediated erythrocyte destruction.

name: membraneous glomerulonephritis
description: Glomerulonephritis characterized by diffuse thickening of glomerular capillary basement membranes, due in part to subepithelial deposits of immunoglobulins separated by spikes of basement membrane material,.

name: lipoma
description: Benign neoplasia derived from lipoblasts or lipocytes of white or brown fat. May be angiomatous or hibernomatous. (M- 8850/0).

name: oligodendroglioma
description: Benign or malignant neoplasm derived form oligodendrocytes (M-9450/3).

name: xanthoma
description: Dermal, subcutaneous,  or tendinous lesions characterized by accumulations of lipid-laden macrophages often rich in cholesterol.

name: adenofibroma
description: A benign neoplasm composed of glandular and fibrous tissues, predominantly glandular. (M-9013/0).

name: lipid depletion
description: Reduction in cellular or plasma lipid content.

name: follicular adenocarcinoma
description: Originates in the follicular cells of thyroid follicles. Papillary, solid and follicular forms. (M- 8330/3).

name: ossifying fibroma
description: Ossifying fibromas are benign tumors derived from pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells or osteoblasts. Occur spontaneously or in response to radiation. Preferentially located in mandible, maxilla and caudal spine. Composed of a characteristically regular trabecular bone pattern embedded in a fibrous stroma. Proliferating component consists of spindle cells which give rise to cuboidal osteoblasts to form rounded bodies or trabeculae. Bone trabeculae resemble the alphabet soup shapes characteristic of fibrous dysplasia in humans. In contrast to fibrous dysplasia the bone trabeculae of ossifying fibroma are mostly lamellar and ringed by active osteoblasts.

name: incomplete closure
description: Incomplete closure of a void or lumen due to failure of growth or fusion of bounding walls.

name: acidophilic macrophage pneumonia
description: A mixed inflammatory infiltrate in the pulmonary airways with predominant intra-alveolar macrophage component with intra- and extracellular, elongated, bright eosinophilic/acidophilic crystals.

name: sertoli-leydig cell tumor
description: Tumor of the ovary or testis containing granulosa or theca cell elements with a tubular componant of Sertoli cell type and producing simultaneous androgenic and estrogenic effects. (M-8631/0).

name: cavernous lymphangioma
description: Large numbers of thin-walled dilated lymphatic channels situated in the dermis, subcutis or skeletal muscle.

name: hydropic degeneration
description: Form of degenerative process in which there is Intracytoplasmic fluid accumulation secondary to disturbance of cell membrane integrity.

name: fibroblast proliferation
description: Abnormal or reactive proliferation of fibroblasts.

name: melanocytic tumor
description: Tumors derived from melanocytes.

name: histiocytosis
description: Benign proliferation of histiocytes.

name: circulatory disorder
description: Lesions leading to or consequent on failure of, or atypical movement of, blood throughout the body.

name: type IV hypersensitivity
description: An antigen-elicited cellular immune reaction that results in tissue damage, but does not require Ab participation. The response is seen at the area of contact.

name: systemic embolism
description: Production of systemic vessel occlusion by emboli released from the left side of the heart, or the aorta.

name: alveolar soft part sarcoma
description: Malignant tumor of unknown origin though probably myogenic due to expression of MyoD and other myogenic lineage markers. Consists of grouped polygonal tumor cells with granular eosinophilic cytoplasm arranged in an organ-like configuration separated by thin fibrovascular septa. Central areas within these nests of cells become necrotic, and the loss of architecture produces an alveolar appearance. (M-9581/3).

name: chondroblastoma, malignant
description: chondroblastoma, malignant

name: leiomyoma
description: Benign neoplasm derived from smooth muscle cells. (M-8890/0).

name: mullerian mixed tumor
description: Neoplasm usually of the uterus or adnexae containing carcinomatous and sarcomatous elements, sometimes with third or fourth components. (M-8950/3).

name: schwannoma
description: May be malignant or benign, Schwann cell derived tumor considered to be neurectodermal with some acquired mesenchymal features. (M-9560/0).

name: communication defect
description: Failure of two cavities, voids or lumens to connect.

name: bronchioloalveolar carcinoma
description: Malignant epithelial neoplasm of the lung. (M-8250/3) 1.2.3.2, 1.2.3.5 of MMHCC classification.

name: zenker's necrosis
description: Degenerative changes in skeletal muscle including hyalinization, swelling, fragmentation, vacuolation eventually resulting in death of muscle fibers.

name: growth arrest
description: The cessation of fetal or embryonic growth beyond a particular stage.

name: intraductal papillomatosis
description: Diffuse multiple adenomatous papillomas derived from the ductal epithelium of the breast. (M- 8505/0).

name: erosion
description: Partial epithelial denudation not penetrating to the basement membrane.

name: renal interstitial mineralisation
description: Small foci of mineralization within the interstitium between tubules.

name: granulocytic sarcoma
description: Solid tumor mass composed predominantly of granulocytic or relatively undifferentiated non-lymphoid haematopoietic cells.

name: organ specific developmental defect
description: Developmental defect characteristic of a particular organ or organ system which may be a recognised syndrome or a complex defect showing multiple manifestations.

name: pinealoma
description: Originating from differentiated cells of the pineal parenchyma. Not to be confused with human pinealoma (syn: germinoma) non-gonadal germ cell tumors found in the pineal believed to be atypical teratomas. May be benign or malignant. If ectopic teratomas/teratocarcinomas use MP322 or MP321. (M-9360/1).

name: Myeloma
description: Plasma cell myeloma - (ICD-O 9732/3).

name: megakaryocytic leukaemia
description: Leukaemia with at least 50% of megakaryocytic cells infiltrating haematopoietic tissue.

name: precursor B -cell lymphoblastic lymphoma/leukaemia
description: Lymphoma originating in a precursor B-cell.

name: blister
description: A collection of fluid underneath the top layer of skin (epidermis).

name: varices
description: An enlarged and often tortuous vein.

name: hepatocellular adenoma
description: Benign neoplasm derived from hepatocytes. (M- 8170/0).

name: placental abnormality
description: Defect in placental growth, differentiation of circulation; maternal or embryonic component.

name: vacuolation
description: Generation of intracytoplasmic vacuoles otherwise unspecified.

name: neuroendocrine tumor
description: Neoplasms derived from the neuroendocrine system.

name: atrial embolism
description: Occlusion of the outflow tract of the right atrium by a thrombus.

name: anaplastic carcinoma
description: carcinoma with an absence of epithelial structural differentiation.

name: growth and differentiation defect
description: Defects in growth (changes in proliferation or mass) and differentiation of cells tissues or organs.

name: lymphangioma
description: Benign hamartomatous malformation of the lymphatic ducts. Usually found in the skin and may be superficial or deep. (M-9170/0).

name: goblet cell hyperplasia
description: Benign proliferation of goblet cells.

name: nerve sheath tumor
description: Neoplasms of the nerve sheath.

name: squamous cell carcinoma
description: Malignant tumor derived from stratified squamous cells. (M-8070/3).

name: drusen
description: Tiny yellow or white deposits of  lamellar or amorphous extracellular material that build up between retina and retinal pigment epithelium.

name: coagulation necrosis
description: A type of necrosis in which the affected cells or tissue are reduced to homogeneous eosinophilic mass without nuclear staining, as a result of the protein coagulation, eg. Infarct. Tissue architecture persists.

name: Harderian gland carcinoma
description: Malignant tumor derived form acinar epithelium of the Harderian gland.

name: gastric forestomach papillomatous hyperplasia
description: The forestomach of the mouse is lined by stratified squamous epithelia. At the limiting ridge there is hyperplasia to various degrees in which this epithelium proliferates to form raised areas on thin fibrovascular stalks.

name: primary immunodeficiency disease
description: Disease due to primary molecular or cellular defect in the immune system or its development.

name: myeloproliferative disease-like myeloid leukaemia
description: Leukaemia in which neoplastic cells are well differentiated and in which there are fewer than 20% blasts.

name: perforation
description: Presence of a hole/channel through a normally imperforate structure often a membrane or septum.

name: myoepithelioma
description: Tumor originating in myoepithelial cells of exocrine glandular structures; for example mammary gland, salivary gland and preputial/clitoral glands. (M-8982/0).

name: intestinal amyloidosis
description: The lamina propria is distended with amorphous hyalinized material interpreted to be amyloid protein.

name: adnexal and skin appendage tumor
description: Tumors of the skin, its constituent structures and glands including the mammary gland, apocrine and eccrine glands, hair follicles and associated structures.

name: Lymphoid neoplasms
description: Neoplasms of the B or T cell lineage.

name: valve defect
description: Malformation of the membranous folds of the heart that prevent reflux of fluid.

name: uretolithiasis
description: Formation or urinary concretions in the ureter.

name: endoplasmic reticulum defect
description: Defect in the structure or function of the endoplasmic reticulum.

name: diffuse large B-cell lymphoma, histiocyte associated
description: Diffuse large B-cell lymphoma with more than 50% histiocytes.

name: goitre
description: Increase in size of the thyroid gland caused initially by uniform follicular epithelial hyperplasia generally in response to iodine deficiency.

name: naevus
description: Local lesion of the skin, often colored by hyperpigmentation or increased vascularity. May be predominantly epidermal, adnexal, melanocytic, vascular, or mesodermal, or a compound overgrowth of these tissues. Not necessarily pre-malignant. (M-8720/0).

name: small T-cell lymphoma
description: Accumulation of small mature T cells. No human counterpart known to date.

name: subacute inflammation
description: transition between acute and chronic inflammation.

name: esthesioneuroblastoma
description: A neoplasm of immature, poorly differentiated neuronal cells believed to arise from neuroepithelial precursors in the olfactory epithelium. (M- 9522/3).

name: hematoma
description: A localised deposition of clotted or partially clotted extravasated blood.

name: foreign body acute pododermatitis
description: acute inflammation of the footpad caused by foreign body.

name: odontoma
description: Hamartomatous malformation of odontogenic tissue. It may vary from nondescript masses of dental tissue (complex odontoma) to multiple well-formed teeth (compound odontoma). Cf ameloblastic fibro-odontoma. (M-9280/0).

name: hyperplasia
description: An increase in cell numbers in comparison to normal as a consequence of increased cell proliferation. Non -neoplastic process.

name: botryomycosis
description: Chronic granulomatous bacterial infection that affects the skin, and sometimes the viscera. Usually caused by S. aureus.

name: neoplasia
description: The pathological process that results in the formation and growth of a neoplasm.

name: lymphoid hyperplasia
description: Benign enlargement of lymphoid tissues.

name: truncoconal septal defect
description: Septal defect lying between the aorta and pulmonary trunks caused by failure of the spiral septum to separate the truncus arteriosus.

name: cell death
description: Complete and irreversible cessation of metabolic activity.

name: trophoblastic tumor
description: Tumors derived directly from trophoblastic tissue or differentiated from germ cell tumor origins.

name: vasculitis
description: Inflammation of a blood vessel.

name: glaucoma; angle closure
description: Develops when the angle caused by the iris and cornea closes. May occur because of anatomically narrow angles or adhesions.

name: muscle regeneration
description: Linear palisaiding of nuclei within thin pale muscle fibers suggestive of repair.

name: chronic inflammation
description: Chronic inflammatory condition characterised by infiltration of primarily lymphocytes.

name: focal hepatic coagulative necrosis
description: Focal necrosis in the liver often but not always associated with thrombosis.

name: eccrine papillary adenoma
description: Papillary form of eccrine sweat gland adenoma. (M -8408/0).

name: process of degenerative change
description: A pathological process of loss or degradation of function, or structural integrity, of a tissue, organ or cell.

name: splenic marginal zone lymphoma
description: A lymphoid proliferation of cells of the marginal zone of the white pulp of the spleen.

name: intervertebral disk prolapse ventral
description: Ventral prolapse of the intervertebral disk.

name: arthrosis
description: Changes characterized by erosion of articular cartilage, either primary or secondary to trauma or other conditions. Not primarily an inflammatory process.

name: anaplastic plasmacytoma
description: Diffuse proliferation of immature plasma cells or plasma blasts.

name: mucous secretions
description: Extracellular accumulation of mucous secretions.

name: anopthalmia
description: Absence of eye.

name: cementifying fibroma
description: Benign neoplasm derived from pluripotential mesenchymal cells or cementoblasts. Well demarcated tumor occurring exclusively in the jaw containing spindle cells which undergo transformation to cuboidal cementoblasts forming multiple cementicle like bodies. ( M-9274/0).

name: thyroid C-cell adenoma
description: Benign neoplasm derived from the calcitonin producing C-cells of the thyroid gland.

name: developmental hypertrophy
description: Increase of the size or cellularity of an organ or tissue as a consequence of loss of normal regulation of cell proliferation.

name: osteofibroma
description: Benign neoplasm derived from pluripotential mesenchymal stem cells or osteoblasts composed of mature nbone trabelculae seperated by a stroma of spindle cells. (M- 9262/0).

name: intraductal hyperplasia
description: Benign hyperplasia of the ducts of the mammary gland. Ducts exhibit more than the usual two layer epithelium (inner cuboidal to columnar cells; outer layer of myoepithelium) without cytological atypia.

name: hepatic central vein perivascular fibrosis
description: Major hepatic vein surrounded by fibrous connective tissue.

name: concretion
description: Solid material formed by aggregation of discrete units or particles.

name: orthokeratosis
description: Thickening of the anuclear cell layer limited to the stratum corneum, as in a stratified squamous epithelium.

name: pyogranulomatous inflammation
description: An inflammatory process in which there is infiltration of polymorphonuclear cells into a more chronic area of inflammation characterized by mononuclear cells, macrophages, lymphocytes and possibly plasma cells.

name: lipomatous metaplasia
description: Metaplasia resulting in formation of fat cells.

name: cataract; nuclear and cortical
description: Nuclear cataract of developmental origin with tendency to progress with age and involve the cortex and capsule.

name: ductal ectasia
description: Dilation of a ductal structure.

name: ceruminous adenocarcinoma
description: Malignant carcinoma of the ceruminous gland (M-8420/3).

name: phthisis bulbi
description: Collapse of the eye globe associated with degenerative changes.

name: prostate intra-epithelial neoplasia
description: See reference for definition.

name: blood vessel tumor
description: Tumor of venous or arterial vessels or capillaries.

name: mitochondrial defect
description: Defect in the structure or function of the mitochondria.

name: psammoma body
description: Round , often laminar, non-proteinaceous eosinophilic bodies representing calcium deposition.

name: bile deposition
description: Intra- or extracellular deposition of bile pigments and their metabolites.

name: T natural killer cell lymphoma
description: Neoplasm of large granular T cells of CD8 phenotype.

name: decalcification
description: Process of loss of calcium from normally calcified tissue, usually bone.

name: mineralisation
description: Deposition of any homogeneous inorganic material.

name: pituicytoma
description: Benign tumor derived from the pituicytes ( glial cells of neurohypophysis) (M-8272/0).

name: mixed glioma
description: Mixed tumor containing astrocytes within an oligodendroglioma or vice versa. In some cases both components may be neoplastic. (M-9382/3).

name: flatus
description: Accumulation or trapping of air

name: gonadoblastoma
description: Gonadal neoplasms that consist of aggregates of germ cells and sex cord elements (M-9073/1).

name: acanthosis
description: Hyperplasia of the Malpighian layer (prickle cell) of the epidermis.
